claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for processing a video stream, comprising:
a Central Processing Unit (CPU);
a memory access controller reading stream data from an external memory under the control of the CPU;
a buffer storing the stream data;
a hardware accelerator encoding or decoding the stream data stored in the buffer under the control of the CPU,
wherein the hardware accelerator comprises:
at least one coder being configured to encode or decode the stream data in accordance with a corresponding one of a plurality of different video coding standards; and
a stream controller receiving the stream data from the buffer and providing a shifted stream data having a predetermined size in response to a bit steam length indicated by the CPU and stream length information.

14. The apparatus of claim 3, wherein the coefficient accelerator comprises:
a plurality of coefficient coders, each of the coefficient coders being configured to conduct a coefficient encoding operation or a coefficient decoding operation in response to the coefficient index signal;
into one of the coefficient coders in response to the coefficient index signal;
a fourth multiplexer outputting the encoded or the decoded coefficient from a coefficient coder of the coefficient coders corresponding to the coefficient index signal; and
a fifth multiplexer outputting one of bit stream length information of the coefficient coder in response to the coefficient index signal to the CPU,
wherein the at least one coder includes the coefficient coders.

15. The apparatus of claim 3, wherein the hardware accelerator comprises:
a register group being configured to include at least one table index register stored the table index signal;
a syntax register being configured to store the encoded or decoded stream data from the syntax accelerator;
a coefficient index register being configured to store the coefficient index signal from the CPU, and
a completion register being configured to store a completion signal from at least one of the syntax accelerator or the coefficient accelerator.

16. The apparatus of claim 3, wherein the bit stream controller comprises,
a shifter outputting the shifted stream data of the predetermined size from a starting position of the stream data;
a buffer providing the stream data to the shifter;
a pointer generating a pointer value that indicates an output starting position when the shifter outputs the shifted stream data;
a FIFO interface transferring the stream data to the buffer from a FIFO memory;
a pointer checker controlling the FIFO interface in accordance with the point value;
a sixth multiplex selecting one of bit stream length information provided from the CPU, the coefficient accelerator, and the syntax accelerator in response to the selection signal by the CPU; and
an adder providing the pointer with a sum of outputs of the sixth multiplexer and the pointer.
